> The options will work but will not be passed to dependencies. That was made on purpose and is exptected.

I know it not be passed to dependencies. But the options not work. I posted an example. Details as follows：

```
// This is AssetBundle
class ModuleAsset extends AssetBundle
{
    public $basePath = '@webroot';
    public $baseUrl = '@web';
    public $css = [
        ['/css/style.css']
    ];
    public $js = [
        ['/js/jquery.min.js'],
        ['/js/swiper.min.js']
    ];
    public $depends = [
    ];
    public $cssOptions = ['appendTimestamp' => true];
    public $jsOptions = [
        'position' => View::POS_END,
        'appendTimestamp' => true
    ];
}
// When i use it like this,  The '/js/zui.min.js' position and timestamp are not effective.
$view->registerJsFile('/js/zui.min.js',
['depends' => [ModuleAsset::class],'position' => View::POS_HEAD,'appendTimestamp' => true]
);
```
